<table style="background-color:#737E96;height:30px;width:100%"><tr><td style="color:white;font-size:14px">Transfer Owners Help</td></tr></table>
<p>
Transfer Owners is used to mass transfer open activities (tasks and events) and/or open opportunities from one owner to another. 
</p>
<p>
Terminology:
</p>
1. Original Owner: The current owner of open activities or opportunities.<br/>
2. New Owner: The owner to which open activities or opportunities will be transferred.<br/>
3. Open Activities: Open activities include open tasks and open events. Open tasks are those whose Status is considered closed (typically this is where Status equals Completed). Open events are those whose End Date Time is later than the current time.<br/>
4. Open Opportunities: Open opportunities are those whose Stage is considered closed (typically this is Closed Won and Closed Lost).<br/>

<p>
How to:
</p>
1. Select Original Owner by clicking the 'lookup' magnifying glass.<br/>
2. Select New Owner by clicking the 'lookup' magnifying glass.<br/>
3. Tick the Transfer All Open Activities box if you want to transfer all open activities.<br/>
4. Tick the Transfer All Open Opportunities box if you want to transfer all open opportunities.<br/>
5. Click 'OK' on the pop-up window to confirm the action.<br/>
<p>
Please note, transferring the ownership does not that guarantee the new owner will have access to the activity or opportunity. There are various security settings that may affect a user's access to the record.
</p>

